Italian Police Arrest 45 People in Tax-Evasion Inquiry, FT Says

-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 
2011-06-16T04:42:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-16/italian-police-arrest-45-people-in-tax-evasion-inquiry-ft-says.html
Italian authorities have arrested 45
professional people suspected of operating a tax-evasion ring
for hundreds of companies and clients, the Financial Times
reported, citing Nello Rossi, the chief prosecutor.  Properties, cars and luxury yachts have been seized and
police said 600 million euros ($850 million) of tax may have
been evaded, the newspaper reported.  Among those arrested is Cesare Pambianchi, the president of
Confcommercio,  Rome ’s trade association, the FT said, adding
that a lawyer for Pambianchi said his client “would be able to
clarify the situation.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alan Purkiss in  London  on   apurkiss@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 